CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 5, 1957, pg. A1 reads: "For Equality Fight - At the Penn Township home of Dr. William Cuthbert, Chi Delta Mu's current president and former presidents beamed proudly after Atty. Henry R. Smith Jr. (seated left), state president of the NAACP, presented a plaque to signify the group's purchase of a $500 life NAACP membership. members of the professional medical and dental fraternity shown are past presidents Charles Cephus of New Brighton (seated), and standing, Left to right: Dr. Chester Harris, New Kensington; Dr. Leon Hadley, McKeesport; Dr. Max Johnston [sic], Aliquippa, and Dr. McKinley King, the current president of Chi Delta Mu. - Harris Photo.
TitMainTitle: Atty. Henry R. Smith Jr. presenting NAACP lifetime membership plaque to Pi Chapter, Chi Delta Mu members Charles Cephus seated, and standing from left: Dr. Chester Harris, Dr. Leon Hadley, Dr. Max Johnson, and Dr. McKinley King, posed in home of Dr. William Cuthbert, Penn Township
